 from a double diminutive of   More   2 ‘Moor’. Compare   Moret  ."]},{"name":"Murton","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of various places in northern England, all named in Old English as ‘settlement or enclosure at the marsh or moor’, from <i>mōr</i> ‘marsh, fen, moor’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’. There has been considerable confusion with both   Morton   and   Merton  ."]},{"name":"Morten","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): habitational name from Mortagne in La Manche, France. This surname has probably been confused with   Morton  ."]}]},{"name":"Beatrice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["and French form of   Beatrix  , which was quite popular in England during the Middle Ages, and strongly revived in the 19th century. It is most famous as the name of Dante's beloved, and is borne by the elder (  b. 1988 ) of the Duke of York's daughters."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Beatrice Morton was born in 1444, in Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. She married Sir John Blair of that Ilk, 8th Lord of Blair in 1474, in Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. She died in 1503, in Ayrshire, Scotland, at the age of 59."},"et":{"1444–1503":"1444–1503","1457–1513":"1457–1513","1474–1522":"1474–1522","1476–1548":"1476–1548","1478–1547":"1478–1547","1503":"1503","1547":"1547","1513":"1513","1457":"1457","1478":"1478","1522":"1522","1444":"1444","1476":"1476","1474":"1474","about 1478":"umbes 1478","1548":"1548","Ayrshire, Kingdom of Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland","Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Ayrshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","of Middil Auchindrane, Ayr, Scot.":"Ayrshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1444–1503":"1444–1503","1457–1513":"1457–1513","1474–1522":"1474–1522","1476–1548":"1476–1548","1478–1547":"1478–1547","1503":"1503","1547":"1547","1513"